snippet.textDisplay:
Speaking of 5G. 
The other week I was having Dish installed, again (streaming got out of hand with data caps, yay), and he was talking about the potential of a city-wide 5G rollout, not just for phones, but also for home internet. 
I know wireless broadband was a trend lately, not tower to home but like a city-wide mesh implementation, but I didn't know that ISPs could piggyback on the 5G network for this. 
Not sure if this idea is genius or scary.
